      "content": "So you're saying that even with the exact same credentials, the name itself is a factor that makes him less likely to succeed? If we were actually using this for recruiting, wouldn't that just be reinforcing systemic bias instead of measuring actual skill? Elaborate on why you think name-based perception is a valid metric for \"likelihood of success.\"",
